format: This data frame contains the following columns:

parameters.Eth: ethnic background: Aboriginal or Not, ("A" or "N").
parameters.Age:
age group: Primary ("F0"), or forms "F1,"
"F2" or "F3".
parameters.Lrn:
learner status: factor with levels Average or Slow learner, ("AL" or
"SL").
parameters.Days: days absent from school in the year.

reference:
S. Quine, quoted in Aitkin, M. (1978) The analysis of unbalanced cross
classifications (with discussion).
Journal of the Royal Statistical Society series A 141, 195–223.
description:
Description
The quine data frame has 146 rows and 5 columns.
Children from Walgett, New South Wales, Australia, were classified by
Culture, Age, Sex and Learner status and the number of days absent from
school in a particular school year was recorded.
title: Absenteeism from School in Rural New South Wales
